## Context
The harness norm "cite only what you keep locally" (prose scholarly-integrity
rule; memory `reference_cited_works_local_docs_articles`) had no enforcement.
After #893/#899 indexed docs/articles into main.bib, 75 of 98 cited works have
local fulltext. This ticket turns the norm into a CI-enforced exit condition and
records the 23-work gap as an explicit allowlist.

Sibling of 0188 (which fixes wrong DOIs). This one is about coverage, not
correctness.

## Relevant files
- `tests/test_cited_works_available.py` — the gate (added here).
- `config/no-fulltext-allowlist.txt` — accepted exceptions (added here).
- `content/bibliography/main.bib`, `content/*.qmd` — inputs.

## Actions (done in this PR)
1. Add the test: every `@key` cited in content/*.qmd that resolves to a bib
   entry must carry a `file=` field OR be allowlisted.
2. Seed the allowlist with the 23 currently-unattainable cited works
   (paywalled books/articles, tool/blog cites, 2 flagged for verification).

## Test
`tests/test_cited_works_available.py` — three checks: coverage (no cited work
lacks fulltext and allowlist), no-redundant-allowlist (an allowlisted key that
gained fulltext must be removed), allowlist-entries-are-real-keys.

## Verification
- [ ] `uv run pytest tests/test_cited_works_available.py` passes.
- [ ] Adding a new `@cite` for a work with no PDF and no allowlist entry fails
      the test.

## Invariants
- `make check-fast` passes; test is unit (no subprocess/network).

## Exit criteria
- The gate is in CI and green. Reducing the allowlist (acquiring the paywalled
  works via bibCNRS/ISTEX/Click&Read) is ongoing housekeeping tracked separately,
  not a blocker for this ticket.
